place.name: ST LAWRENCE
place.gazetteerText: LAWRENCE (ST.), a parish in Haverfordwest district, Pembroke; on the river Cleddau, 7 miles NW of Clarbeston Road r. station, and 8 N by W of Haverfordwest. Post town, Wolfs-Castle, under Haverfordwest. Acres, 1, 751. Real property, £904. Pop., 205. Houses, 41. The property is much subdivided. The living is a rectory in the diocese of St. Davids. Value, £80. * Patron, the Lord Chancellor. The church was reported in 1859 as not good. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
